================================================================================
Adding a new bundled grammar
================================================================================
1. Fetch the grammar's `.wasm`, `LICENSE`, and `queries/tags.scm` from the
   pinned upstream tag (e.g., a GitHub release tag on
   `github.com/tree-sitter/tree-sitter-<lang>`).
2. Verify the LICENSE file is MIT or Apache-2.0. Refuse anything stricter
   (GPL, LGPL, etc.) — those are incompatible with shipping inside an
   Apache-2.0 npm package.
3. Vendor under `vendor/tree-sitter/<lang>/`.
4. Compute the WASM file's sha256, add an entry to this NOTICE file with
   the same shape as the entries above.
5. Add the language config to `src/wiki/api-extractor/tree-sitter-extractor.ts`.
